<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="null.php" src="/usr/local/Cellar/php55/5.5.5/lib/php/Mail/null.php"><scope classrefs="Mail" doc="Null implementation of the PEAR Mail:: interface.&#10;@access public&#10;@package Mail&#10;@version $Revision: 294747 $" ilk="class" line="52" lineend="84" name="Mail_null"><scope doc="Implements Mail_null::send() function. Silently discards all&#10;mail.&#10;&#10;@param mixed $recipients Either a comma-seperated list of recipients&#10;             (RFC822 compliant), or an array of recipients,&#10;             each RFC822 valid. This may contain recipients not&#10;             specified in the headers, for Bcc:, resending&#10;             messages, etc.&#10;&#10;@param array $headers The array of headers to send with the mail, in an&#10;             associative array, where the array key is the&#10;             header name (ie, 'Subject'), and the array value&#10;             is the header value (ie, 'test'). The header&#10;             produced from those values would be 'Subject:&#10;             test'.&#10;&#10;@param string $body The full text of the message body, including any&#10;              Mime parts, etc.&#10;&#10;@return mixed Returns true on success, or a PEAR_Error&#10;              containing a descriptive error message on&#10;              failure.&#10;@access public" ilk="function" line="79" lineend="82" name="send" returns="mixed" signature="mixed send(mixed $recipients, array $headers, string $body)"><variable citdl="mixed" ilk="argument" line="79" name="recipients" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="79" name="headers" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="79" name="body" /></scope></scope></scope>